Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp; rose symbol
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.80,11. Name Aristomachos? Perhaps from the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0046.02.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0922)
